{"id": 7238, "source": "pestle", "subject": "chemistry", "course": null, "level": "SL", "paper": "2", "year": "2017", "session": "17N", "subtopic": "1-2-the-mole-concept, 1-3-reacting-masses-and-volumes", "title": "17N.2.SL.TZ0.4", "topic_id": "1", "source_url": "https://pestle.pages.dev/app/", "question_html": "<div class=\"specification\">\n<p>Menthol is an organic compound containing carbon, hydrogen and oxygen.</p>\n</div><div class=\"question\" style=\"padding-left: 20px; padding-right: 20px;\">\n<p>Complete combustion of 0.1595 g of menthol produces 0.4490 g of carbon dioxide and 0.1840 g of water. Determine the empirical formula of the compound showing your working.</p>\n<div class=\"marks\">[3]</div>\n<div class=\"question_part_label\">a.</div>\n</div><div class=\"question\" style=\"padding-left: 20px; padding-right: 20px;\">\n<p>0.150 g sample of menthol, when vaporized, had a volume of 0.0337 dm<sup>3</sup> at 150 °C and 100.2 kPa. Calculate its molar mass showing your working.</p>\n<div class=\"marks\">[2]</div>\n<div class=\"question_part_label\">b.</div>\n</div>", "solution_html": "<div class=\"question\" style=\"padding-left: 20px;\">\n<p>carbon: «<span class=\"mjpage\"><math alttext=\"\\frac{{0.4490\\,{\\text{g}}}}{{44.01\\,{\\text{g}}\\,{\\text{mo}}{{\\text{l}}^{ - 1}}}}\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\">\n<mfrac>\n<mrow>\n<mn>0.4490</mn>\n<mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n<mrow>\n<mtext>g</mtext>\n</mrow>\n</mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mn>44.01</mn>\n<mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n<mrow>\n<mtext>g</mtext>\n</mrow>\n<mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n<mrow>\n<mtext>mo</mtext>\n</mrow>\n<mrow>\n<msup>\n<mrow>\n<mtext>l</mtext>\n</mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mo>−</mo>\n<mn>1</mn>\n</mrow>\n</msup>\n</mrow>\n</mrow>\n</mfrac>\n</math></span>» = 0.01020 «mol» / 0.1225 «g»</p>\n<p><em><strong>OR</strong></em></p>\n<p>hydrogen: «<span class=\"mjpage\"><math alttext=\"\\frac{{0.1840 \\times 2}}{{18.02}}\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\">\n<mfrac>\n<mrow>\n<mn>0.1840</mn>\n<mo>×</mo>\n<mn>2</mn>\n</mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mn>18.02</mn>\n</mrow>\n</mfrac>\n</math></span>» = 0.02042 «mol» / 0.0206 «g»</p>\n<p>oxygen: «0.1595 – (0.1225 + 0.0206)» = 0.0164 «g» / 0.001025 «mol»</p>\n<p>empirical formula: C<sub>10</sub>H<sub>20</sub>O</p>\n<p><em>Award <strong>[3]</strong> for correct final answer.</em></p>\n<div class=\"question_part_label\">a.</div>\n</div><div class=\"question\" style=\"padding-left: 20px;\">\n<p>temperature = 423 K</p>\n<p><em><strong>OR</strong></em></p>\n<p>«<em>M</em> <span class=\"mjpage\"><math alttext=\" = \\frac{{mRT}}{{pV}}\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\">\n<mo>=</mo>\n<mfrac>\n<mrow>\n<mi>m</mi>\n<mi>R</mi>\n<mi>T</mi>\n</mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mi>p</mi>\n<mi>V</mi>\n</mrow>\n</mfrac>\n</math></span></p>\n<p>«<em>M </em><span class=\"mjpage\"><math alttext=\" = \\frac{{0.150\\,{\\text{g}} \\times 8.31\\,{\\text{J}} {{\\text{ K}}^{ - 1}}\\,{\\text{mol}}{}^{ - 1} \\times 423\\,{\\text{K}}}}{{100.2\\,{\\text{kPa}} \\times 0.0337\\,{\\text{d}}{{\\text{m}}^3}}} = \" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\">\n<mo>=</mo>\n<mfrac>\n<mrow>\n<mn>0.150</mn>\n<mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n<mrow>\n<mtext>g</mtext>\n</mrow>\n<mo>×</mo>\n<mn>8.31</mn>\n<mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n<mrow>\n<mtext>J</mtext>\n</mrow>\n<mrow>\n<msup>\n<mrow>\n<mtext> K</mtext>\n</mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mo>−</mo>\n<mn>1</mn>\n</mrow>\n</msup>\n</mrow>\n<mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n<mrow>\n<mtext>mol</mtext>\n</mrow>\n<msup>\n<mrow>\n</mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mo>−</mo>\n<mn>1</mn>\n</mrow>\n</msup>\n<mo>×</mo>\n<mn>423</mn>\n<mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n<mrow>\n<mtext>K</mtext>\n</mrow>\n</mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mn>100.2</mn>\n<mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n<mrow>\n<mtext>kPa</mtext>\n</mrow>\n<mo>×</mo>\n<mn>0.0337</mn>\n<mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n<mrow>\n<mtext>d</mtext>\n</mrow>\n<mrow>\n<msup>\n<mrow>\n<mtext>m</mtext>\n</mrow>\n<mn>3</mn>\n</msup>\n</mrow>\n</mrow>\n</mfrac>\n<mo>=</mo>\n</math></span>» 156 «g mol<sup>–1</sup>»</p>\n<p><em>Award <strong>[1]</strong> for correct answer with no working shown.</em></p>\n<p><em>Accept “pV = nRT <strong>AND</strong> n = <span class=\"mjpage\"><math alttext=\"\\frac{m}{M}\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\">\n<mfrac>\n<mi>m</mi>\n<mi>M</mi>\n</mfrac>\n</math></span>” for M1.</em></p>\n<div class=\"question_part_label\">b.</div>\n</div>", "examiners_html": "<div class=\"question\" style=\"padding-left: 20px;\">\n[N/A]\n<div class=\"question_part_label\">a.</div>\n</div><div class=\"question\" style=\"padding-left: 20px;\">\n[N/A]\n<div class=\"question_part_label\">b.</div>\n</div>"}